Sprague Avenue, east side, between Surf Avenue and Clermont Avenue. This house was owned by Captain Martin in 1874; by James Steel in 1898; by Catherine McDonald in 1907, and by the Rully Realty Co. in 1917.
August 8, 1936
P. L. Sperr
